[size=18pt][color=#6B46C1][b]Why Mainnet 2026.2?[/b][/color][/size]
[hr]

Fellow cypherpunks,

Mainnet 2026.1 launched February 15 and proved the network works. Blocks were produced, miners connected, the DEX ran, AI inference functioned. But the transition from testnet wasn't clean enough. Data contamination from the testnet-to-mainnet migration caused:

[list]
[li]Emission controller state not properly rebuilt from genesis[/li]
[li]Stale testnet balances persisting through the purge[/li]
[li]Mining reward oscillation from incorrect correction factors[/li]
[/list]

Rather than patch around contaminated state, we made the engineering decision to do what Bitcoin would do: [b]start clean[/b]. Mainnet 2026.2 launches from a fresh data directory with new identity keys, new chain ID, and complete P2P isolation from the old network.

[b]This is not a failure - it's quality engineering.[/b] We identified the contamination vectors, built isolation mechanisms, and are relaunching with zero legacy state.


