[size=18pt][color=#6B46C1][b]P2P Isolation: How We Prevent Contamination[/b][/color][/size]
[hr]

Three new isolation mechanisms ensure zero cross-network contamination:

[b]1. Gossipsub Topic Isolation[/b]
Old nodes subscribe to /qnk/mainnet2026.1/* topics. New nodes use /qnk/mainnet2026.2/*. They never see each other's messages.

[b]2. Protocol Handshake Validation[/b]
The libp2p handshake now validates network_id. Connections from mainnet2026.1 nodes are rejected before any data exchange.

[b]3. HTTP State Sync network_id Field[/b]
The FullStateSnapshot now includes a network_id field. Snapshots from different networks are rejected on receipt. Old binaries without this field are also rejected.


